@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Batonnade" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  The game board consists of an 8 by 8 spaces area occupied by sets
of vertical or horizontal bars and each set can have between 1 to 4
bars.

  The goal is to create series of sets of bars. A series is an
alignment of 8 sets of horizontal bars in a row or 8 sets of
vertical bars in a column. Each set of bars from a series must have
one bar more or less than the number of bars on either side in the
series.

  When you click on a position that contains one or more bars, the
number of bars will increase by one unit. When there are 4 bars and
you click again, these bars will be replaced by one bar in the
other direction, and the number of bars will increase up to 4, and
so on...

  When a series of sets of bars is completed, the sets of bars that
have the least amount of bars will be eliminated and will be
replaced by small square dots. The number of bars from the
remaining sets will decrease by one unit. The number of points you
get will vary according to the total number of bars in the series,
if that number is under 17, you will one point. The more bars there
are, the higher the number of points you will get... especially if
blocks are present on the game board, as the number of points is
multiplied by the number of blocks...

  As the game progresses, blocks will appear from time to time, but
none of them will be in line with another block. When the 8th block
appears on the board, the game ends...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

